<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1460">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/156.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram March 15. It is proper to protest in behalf of Americans
                            against a tax which is confiscatory or discriminatory, and you are also
                            instructed to use your good offices for the protection of other
                            foreigners against such taxation, but we are not justified in inquiring
                            into its purpose or the use to be made of it if levied by a competent de
                            facto authority. You will constantly bear in mind the fact that
                            injustice done to religious bodies will arouse deep and lasting
                            prejudice against those responsible for it and therefore use such moral
                            influence as is possible against such acts.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>